text: Courcouronnes is a former commune. It is in Île-de-France in the Essonne department in north France. On 1 January 2019, it was merged into the new commune of Évry-Courcouronnes. In 2018, 13,490 people lived there. The commune is in the southern suburbs of Paris, from the center. The aerospace company Arianespace is headquartered in Courcouronnes. == References == Category:Former communes in Essonne Category:Évry-Courcouronnes
